12.title: Debrief
12.content:
Thank you for volunteering your time to complete our study!

As mentioned before, this research study attempts to create a better understanding of how semantic networks are formed and, by extension, how learning of words and word associations occur. Shedding light on such semantic networks will enable better comprehension of the brain and cognitive processes.

If you wish to withdraw your participation from this experiment, kindly contact the principal investigator as listed below within the next 48 hours. You will still receive full credit and reimbursement for your participation. Please do so within the next 48 hours as any identifying information will be discarded after that and it would no longer be possible to locate and remove your data. The principal investigatorâ€™s contact is as follows:

Name: Jazton Chern Jie Sern
Contact No.: (+65) 83226303
Email: jazton@nus.edu.sg

This is an ongoing study that is expected to be completed in May 2022. If you find interest in the research and would like to be updated about the progress and subsequent findings, you are invited to communicate with the principal investigator for more details and updates.

Once again, thank you for your time and participation in this study.

Please do not close this window.
This window will close automatically in 30s and you will be redirected to receive your participation credit then.
Do contact the principal investigator if your participation credit is not awarded to you.

4. I will not have any financial benefits that result from the commercial development of this research.
5. I consent to have the coded data made available for future research studies. This will be subject to an Institutional Review Boardâ€™s approval.

Reminder: If you do not agree to any of the above, please feel free to stop the study and contact the principal investigator.
